Robert Johnson is Lieutenant in a black unit of the Union army, former slave, and Iola’s long-lost uncle. Robert is literate, articulate, hard working, and courageous. He rallies the slaves in their efforts to abandon the plantations, owns a successful business, and quickly rises in the army’s ranks. Generous and forgiving, Robert offers financial support to his former slave mistress after the Civil War dismantles the slave system and her plantation, leaving her destitute. Robert is also a mulatto who could pass as white.